snippet.textDisplay:
I know people here are probably annoyed by correction comments, but this isn't actually (directly) about the Billie VS Melanie thing so- here's a quick little PSA/rant/thing

A lot of people have been pointing out that Billie and Melanie aren't the only people who made songs named "Copycat" and citing the Vocaloid song of the same name. As a Vocaloid fan, I love that this song is getting mentioned! However, a lot of people are wrongfully crediting the song as being made by Gumi! This is outright wrong! Gumi did NOT make the song! In fact, Gumi isn't even a real person! Gumi is merely a Vocaloid voicebank-- As in, she is a program to SING SONGS FOR YOU! She does NOT make songs!
The song was ACTUALLY made by VocaCircus (AKA Circus-P)! This especially upsets me as Circus-P happens to be one of my FAVORITE English Vocaloid producers! So please do not miscredit people, otherwise, it's gonna be a repeat of the Wowaka/Hatsune Miku situation (RIP Wowaka)!

PSA is over, continue on with your day!
snippet.textOriginal:
